Inspired by gluons in an atom's nucleus and how they bond quarks to form protons and nucleons hence sustaining the atom's existence, we at Gluon Electronik bond engineerable problems with their electronic engineering solutions and the solutions to their end market. This is part of an effort to contribute to the harmony between humanity and technology all while safe-guarding the environment to improve quality of life and improve operations in industries. We develop, maintain and repair electronic hardware, firmware and software to create and improve solutions to both real life and cutting-edge problems. Our primary areas of focus include;

1. Acquisition of sensor data for various applications and the IoTization of it such that it can be remotely monitored

2. Biosignal capturing and processing: We collect and condition various biosignals from the human body including; sEMG, EOG, ECG and EEG signals with specially designed DAQs and utilise the signals for robotic control and medical assessment purposes using AI to create prosthetics for the handicapped, cobots for industrial safety and health assesment/monitoring kits.
